<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Conduct2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Conduct,</orth> vb. 1) to bring along, to attend: <bibl n="shak. mm 2.3.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 3, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 2.96" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL II, 96</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.374" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 374</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.4.58" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 4, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.1.107" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 1, 107.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. aww 3.5.44" default="NO" valid="yes">All's III, 5, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 2.2.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 2, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.6.43" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 6, 43</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 4.103" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 IV, 103</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.7.51" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 7, 51</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.5.100" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 100</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.4.73" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 4, 73</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.103" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 103</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.4.58" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 4, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 3.2.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 2, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.2.184" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 184</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.6.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 6, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.7.7" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 7, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.79" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.6.29" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 6, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.333" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 3, 333</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.3.108" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 3, 108</bibl>.<lb />2) to lead as a commander: <cit><quote>will he c. you through the heart of France,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.8.38" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 8, 38</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>hasten his musters and c. his powers,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 4.2.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 2, 16</bibl></cit>.
